==English==
===Noun===
'''Mistress'''

#{{archaic}} Used as the title of a married woman before her name. Now used only in the abbreviated form '''[[Mrs]]'''.

====Quotations====
'''1855 &ndash; 1857''': The sound of Mistress Affery cautiously chaining the door before she opened it, caused them both to look that way. &mdash; ''Little Dorrit'', Charles Dickens, Book 2, Chapter 10

